prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Display price and description of each item",
      "evidence_quote": "The cash register displays the price of each item and its description."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Indicate end of sale",
      "evidence_quote": "When all the purchases are recorded, the cashier indicates the end of the sale."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Display total cost of purchases",
      "evidence_quote": "The cash register displays the total cost of the purchases."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Calculate change for customer payment",
      "evidence_quote": "the cash register indicates how much change the customer is to be given"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Verify customer financial solvency via authorisation centre (cheque payment)",
      "evidence_quote": "the cashier verifies that the customer is financially solvent by sending a request to an authorisation centre via the cash register;"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Send request for authorisation to authorisation centre (credit card payment)",
      "evidence_quote": "a banking terminal forms part of the cash register. It sends a request for authorisation to an authorisation centre, according to the card type."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Record sale and print receipt",
      "evidence_quote": "The cash register records the sale and prints a receipt."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Send information on number of items sold to stock management system",
      "evidence_quote": "When the payment transaction is finished, the cash register sends the information on the number of items sold to the stock management system."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Initialise cash registers for day (shop manager)",
      "evidence_quote": "Every morning, the shop manager initialises the cash registers for the day."
    }
  ]
}

